<div id="banner">
	<h1>got spam?</h1>
</div>

<div class="content">
<p>Well, do you? If you&#8217;ve been collecting your spam for a while (as I have), then <a href="http://paulgraham.com/wantspam.html">Paul Graham wants it</a> for his filtering work. They&#8217;ll make it public or not and remove anything specific to you. The best part is that all your spam goes to making his filters better to stop more spam in the future.</p>

<p class="posted">posted September 01, 2002 10:13 PM (<a class="category" href="http://www.aaronsw.com/weblog/cat_technology">Technology</a>)  <a href="000554" rel="bookmark">#</a></p>
</div>

